article.headline: Brown 76, New Hampshire 64
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Forward Mark MacDonald scored 19 of his career-high 25 points in the first half as Brown won its fourth straight game, 76-64, over New Hampshire. MacDonald shot 10-of-12 from the floor, including 3-of-4 from three-point range. Sophomore P.J. Flaherty added a career-high 11 points for the Bears, and freshman Damon Huffman also had 11. Blagoj Janev and Ben Sturgill each had 12 points for the Wildcats (4-3), and Sturgill also had a game-high 11 rebounds. New Hampshire cut a nine-point deficit to 68-64 on Jermaine Anderson's jump shot late in the second half. But Brown (4-4) outscored New Hampshire 8-0 over the final 1:14 as MacDonald put in a missed shot, dunked off a fast-break pass from Jason Forte and fed Huffman for a layup. Forte clinched the victory by sinking both ends of a one-and-one free throw opportunity. The Bears led 27-21 with just under seven minutes left in the first half when MacDonald finished off a 10-2 run that gave Brown a 34-23 lead. MacDonald scored on a jump shot and drained a three-point shot. He then hit another three-pointer with 22 seconds left to give Brown a 45-32 halftime lead. Forte, a senior guard, scored nine points and lifted his career total to 1,226 -- 15 points behind Phil Brown and Peter Moss who are tied for ninth place on Brown's all-time list.
